(d) whether the person had the ability to make decisions and give instructions based upon, or otherwise give effect to, such advice as might be received. [16]  25 There is a presumption that a person of full age is capable of managing his or her own affairs, [5] which must include the management of litigation to which he or she is a party. The person who alleges the contrary bears the onus. [6]
